"Governments are trying to reconcile what have traditionally been seen as conflicting objectives – privacy and security. They want to employ the most advanced technologies to help them deliver services and benefits to citizens, but they also want to reduce fraud and increase efficiency. Data protection is at the very heart of this quandary. At the centre of this debate are the standards that governments and others (such as banks, card companies and mobile network operators) should aim to meet, and whether they can attain them. Pat Carroll, CEO of ValidSoft, analyses the current standards of data protection regulation around the world, and offers a solution to raise those standards."
